  </h3>
 </div>
</div>
<div class="wrap2">
 UGA Theatre Ranked #10 as "Best for the Money"
</div>
<div class="views-field views-field-created">
 <span class="field-content">
  Monday, March 4, 2019 - 1:56pm
 </span>
</div>
<div class="views-field views-field-body">
 <div class="field-content">
  <div class="wrap">
   <p>
    The Theatre program at University of Georgia was ranked as a “Best Value for the Money” in the annual nationwide ranking of U.S.
   </p>
  </div>
 </div>
</div>
<div class="views-row">
 <div class="views-field views-field-title">
  <h3 class="field-content">
   <a href="/news/stories/2019/gae-present-johnna-adams-harrowing-drama-gidions-knot">
    <img alt="GK" height="250" src="/sites/default/files/styles/rectangle_350x250/public/2019-02/Gidion%27s%20Knot.jpg?itok=Zm_8lquI" typeof="Image" width="375">
    </img>
   </a>
  </h3>
 </div>
</div>
<div class="wrap2">
 GAE to present Johnna Adams' harrowing drama "Gidion's Knot"
</div>
<div class="views-field views-field-created">
 <span class="field-content">
  Friday, February 22, 2019 - 9:09am
 </span>
</div>
<div class="views-field views-field-body">
 <div class="field-content">
  <div class="wrap">
   <p>
    <span>
     <span>
      ATHENS, GA - The Graduate Acting Ensemble (GAE), a cohort of MFA students in UGA’s department of theatre and film studies, presents Johnna Adams' “Gidion’s Knot”, directed by professor Kristin Kundert.
     </span>
    </span>
   </p>
  </div>
 </div>
</div>
